\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 31.             SALICACEAE}
\par            

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  Edit. J.R. Edmondson.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Dioecious. Trees or shrubs. Leaves alternate, very rarely opposite; stipules present. Flowers subtended by bracts and arranged in catkins; perianth absent; glands present, sometimes nectariferous. Male flowers with 2 to many stamens; filaments filiform, free or more or less united. Female flowers with 1 unilocular carpel with 2-4 parietal placentae; ovules numerous, ascending, anatropous. Fruit a capsule dehiscing by 2-4 valves. Seeds numerous, very small, each with a tuft of long hairs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Literature: R.D. Meikle,{\i  Willows and Poplars of Great Britain and Ireland.} London, 1984.
\par

